 HC move on banning Pratima

New Delhi: The Delhi High Court on Friday sought explanation from the government, Indian Olympic Association (IOA) and Weightlifting Federation of India (WFI) and others on a petition by lifter Pratima Kumari challenging the life ban imposed on her for testing positive for drugs. 

Justice S.K. Kaul issued showcause notices to ministry of youth affairs and sports, IOA, WFI, Sports Authority of India (SAI), M.K. Mishra (CEO of SAI?sS dope control centre, banned national coach Pal Singh Sandhu and Russian coach Leonid Tararnenko, seeking their explanation as to why Pratima?s petition not be entertained. The matter has been fixed for hearing on January 25 next year. 

At the outset of the proceeding, Pratima?s counsel Sushil Dutt Salwan contended that the IOA and WFI are not authorised to take decision of banning the players. 

Life ban has been slapped on Pratima, Sanamacha Chanu and S. Sunaina on the basis of the report of two-member committee comprising K.P. Singh Deo and Manmohan Singh. 

